          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



          SECTION 2.0 INSTRUCTIONS          ________________________

          Instructions to VAL  are divided into  two logical  groups, unprivi-
          leged  and privileged.   A  NETPRIV user  may  enter  any valid  VAL
          instruction.  NETVAL users  may only  execute unprivileged  instruc-
          tions.  The instructions  enable the user to add,  change, or delete
          CUD entries.  NETPRIV instructions have  additional inquiry and com-
          pare capabilities on the CUD entries and read and write capabilities
          on the MUD blocks.   Instructions in each section  are listed alpha-
          betically.  Each instruction description is  followed by an example.
          Instructions exclusively related to the Class Information option are
          so noted.

          Note:  The examples of entries and responses  will be shown with the
                 user input in lower case and  VAL prompts in uppercase.  Com-
                 ments (not  entries or prompts)  are in parentheses.   If you
                 receive responses  that are  not like the  ones shown  in the
                 examples, check Appendix A to  determine whether they are VAL
                 error messages.  If the response is still unique you may have
                 a system error.



          SECTION 2.1 NETVAL (Unprivileged) Instructions          ______________________________________________



          2.1.1 Attach Instruction                __________________

          Syntax:  Attach

          Description:  The attach instruction assigns a magnetic tape unit to
               the user's  slot.   This   must  be   done  before   any  other
               tape instructions  can be  executed.  The  user must  enter the
               tape unit number.

               Example:

                  * attach

                  TAPE UNIT: 1

                  TAPE ATTACHED

                  *











                                                        INSTRUCTIONS    Page 5


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



          2.1.2 Change Class Instruction                ________________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge CLass

          Description:  The change class instruction changes the definition of
               a class already  assigned  to  a user.  The user must enter the
               username, class position, and class  information (see New Class
               Instruction  subsection 2.1.16).   Class  position  refers   to
               the  relative position of the class the user wants to change in
               the list of classes  for the user.  The first class  for a user
               is position 1, the second is position 2, etc.  The user will be
               requested to redefine the class completely.

               Note:  This instruction  only applies if the  Class Information
                      option is in effect.

               Example:

                  * change class
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  CLASS POSITION: 1     (enter relative position of class
                                        in entry)
                  CLASS: 5
                  GROUP? y
                  GROUP: 5
                  HOME GROUP? y
                  ANOTHER GROUP OR HOST FOR THIS CLASS? n

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.3 Change Control Instruction                __________________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge COntrol

          Description:   The change  control  instruction  resets the  control
               information for a user.   The   user  must  enter  username and
               the settings for the following os:

                    IGNORE COLON
                    LOGIN OVER SHUT
                    NO PASSWORD









                                                        INSTRUCTIONS    Page 6


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Example:

                  * change control
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  LOGIN OVER SHUT? y
                  PASSWORD REQUIRED? n
                  TRANSPARENT GATEWAY LOGON? n
                  IGNORE COLON OPTION? n

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.4 Change District Instruction                ___________________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge District

          Description:  The  change district instruction changes  the district
               for a user.  The user must enter username and district.

               Example:

                  * change district
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  DISTRICT: 1

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.5 Change GAN Instruction                ______________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge Gan

          Description:   The change  GAN  instruction moves  a  user from  one
               global account to another.   The  user  is asked to enter USER-
               NAME and GAN.   The new GAN must  be one that has  already been
               assigned.










                                                        INSTRUCTIONS    Page 7


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Example:

                  * change gan
                  USERNAME: dopler
                  GAN: 123
                  THAT GAN IS UNASSIGNED     (unassigned gan cannot be
                                             used)
                  GAN: 9
                  ILLEGAL CHARACTER ENTERED, TRY AGAIN: 10     (GAN must
                                                               be octal)

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *



          2.1.6 Change Home Instruction                _______________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge Home

          Description:  The  change home instruction  changes the  home system
               for a user.   The user must enter the username  and home system
               number.

               Note:  This instruction  only applies if the  Class Information
                      option is not in effect.

               Example:

                  * change home
                  USERNAME: dopler
                  HOME:  6

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT?

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.7 Change IRC Instruction                ______________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge Irc

          Description:  The  change IRC instruction changes  the international
               record carrier  assignment  for  a user.   The user  must enter
               USERNAME and the new IRC assignment.  Zero (0) is entered if no
               IRC is desired.





                                                        INSTRUCTIONS    Page 8


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Example:

                  * change irc
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  IRC: 5

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.8 Change Name Instruction                _______________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge Name

          Description:  The change  name instruction changes an old  name to a
               new name.  The user  will  be  asked  to enter new username and
               (old) username.  The new username must not be currently valid.

               Example:

                  * change name
                  NEW USERNAME: marcinjill     (enter invalid user)
                  USER ALREADY THERE           (user is already valid)
                  NEW USERNAME: marcinj
                  USERNAME: marcinjill         (enter old username)

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.9 Change Password Instruction                ___________________________

          Syntax:  CHAnge Password

          Description:  The change password instruction assigns a new password
               to a user  name.   The  user must enter  username and password.
               The password change date will be updated to reflect the change.











                                                        INSTRUCTIONS    Page 9


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Example:

                  * change password
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  PASSWORD:
                  ENTER IT AGAIN:

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.10 Check Instruction                 _________________

          Syntax:  CHEck

          Description:  The check instruction determines whether or not a user
               is  already  valid in  the  CUD.   Only  the username  must  be
               entered.

               Example:

                  * check
                  USERNAME: marcinj
                  USER NOT FOUND           (user 'MARCINJ' is not in CUD)
                  *
                  * check
                  USERNAME: flame
                  USER ALREADY THERE       (user 'FLAME' is valid in CUD)
                  *




          2.1.11 Detach Instruction                 __________________

          Syntax:  DETach

          Description:   The detach  instruction deassigns  the magnetic  tape
               unit previously assigned to the slot so that it is available to
               other  slots.  The  quit instruction  automatically performs  a
               detach.

               Example:

                  * detach

                  TAPE DETACHED

                  *



                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 10


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



          2.1.12 Delete Class Instruction                 ________________________

          Syntax:  DELete CLass

          Description:  The delete class  instruction removes a class descrip-
               tion from a  user's  entry.   The user must  enter username and
               class position.  At least one class  definition for a user must
               always remain.

               Note:  This instruction  only applies if the  Class Information
                      option is in effect.
               Example:

                  * delete class
                  USERNAME: testname
                  CLASS POSITION: 0
                  CLASS NOT FOUND     (no class position zero)
                  CLASS POSITION: 3
                  CLASS NOT FOUND     (no class in position 3)
                  CLASS POSITION: 1

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *




          2.1.13 Delete User Instruction                 _______________________

          Syntax:  DELete User

          Description:  The  delete user instruction  removes a  username from
               the CUD.  The user must only enter the USERNAME.

               Example:

                  * delete user
                  USERNAME: marcinjill

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *











