          2.1.15 ID Instruction                 ______________

          Syntax:  ID

          Description:  The ID  instruction rewinds the tape  previously atta-
               ched, identifies the  tape  as  a   CUD  backup tape, and types
               the creation date of the tape.

               Example:

                  * id

                  MTA IS NOT A CUD TAPE   (tape read is not identified as
                                          a CUD tape)

                  * id

                  CUD TAPE RECORDED ON: 06/08/79    1729 GMT

                  *













                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 13


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980





          2.1.16 New Class Instruction                 _____________________

          Syntax:  New CLass

          Description:  The new  class instruction enters an  additional class
               for already  existing username.   The user  must enter  a valid
               username and the class information.  The class information con-
               sists of:

               CLASS: - enter class number
               GROUP? - enter 'Y' to add a group, 'N' to add a host
               GROUP: - enter group number
               HOME GROUP? - enter 'Y' to denote the GROUP as home
               HOST: - enter a host number
               HOME HOST? - enter 'Y' to denote the HOST as home
               ANOTHER GROUP  OR HOST  FOR THIS  CLASS? -  enter 'Y'   to  add
               additional group or host information for the class

               Note:  This instruction  only applies if the  Class Information
                      option is in effect.

               Example:

                  * new class
                  USERNAME: marcinjill
                  CLASS: 0
                  GROUP? n
                  HOST: 1
                  HOME HOST? n
                  NO HOME FOR THIS CLASS     (each class must have a home
                                             described)
                  CLASS: 0
                  GROUP? n
                  HOST: 1
                  HOME HOST? y
                  ANOTHER GROUP OR HOST FOR THIS CLASS? n

                  ALL ENTRIES CORRECT? y

                  ENTRY COMPLETED
                  *













                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 14


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980





          2.1.17 New User Instruction                 ____________________

          Syntax:  New User

          Description:  The new user instruction enters  a brand new name into
               the  CUD.  The  user must  first  decide whether  the new  name
               should be validated in a  global account that  already  exists,
               or   if  the   name   should  be  validated   in  a new  global
               account.   If the  name is  to be  validated in  an old  global
               account,  the user  will be  prompted  for a   user  name  that
               already  exists   in  that  account.    The  user will  then be
               prompted for  username, control  information, password  (twice,
               not  echoed), district,  IRC,  and  class or  home  information
               (depending on which VAL option was chosen).

               The new name is  assigned  the   next  sequential  UUN  availa-
               ble.  UUN's  are  not reused, even  after a username is invali-
               dated.  If the new name is  validated in an old global account,
               it  will   be  assigned  the  same   GAN  as   the  name   that
               already  exists  in that account.   Otherwise, the next sequen-
               tial GAN will be assigned to the user.

































                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 15


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Example:

                  * new user
                  DOES THIS USER BELONG TO A NEW ACCOUNT? n
                  ENTER VALID USER IN ACCOUNT: flame     (not asked if
                                                         new account)
                  USERNAME: abc:123                     (':' is illegal
                                                         character)
                  ILLEGAL CHARACTER ENTERED, TRY AGAIN: abc123
                  ALLOW LOGIN OVER SHUT? n
                  PASSWORD REQUIRED? y     (if 'n', user is not prompted
                                           for password)
                  TRANSPARENT GATEWAY LOGON? n
                  IGNORE COLON OPTION? y
                  PASSWORD:                (password not echoed)
                  ILLEGAL CHARACTER,       (user tried to use a semi-
