          2.1.18 Restore Instruction                 ___________________

          Syntax:  RESTore

          Description:  The  restore instruction  rewinds the  tape previously
               attached, identifies  the   tape  as  a  CUD  backup tape, asks
               the user if he  wants to continue, and if so  writes the CUD to
               disk from tape.


                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 16


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



               Note:  This  is a  very  time consuming  action  and cannot  be
                      interrupted.

               Example:

                  * restore

                  CUD TAPE RECORDED ON: 06/08/79    1729 GMT

                  DO YOU WANT TO CONTINUE? y

                  CUD RESTORED

                  *




          2.1.19 Rewind Instruction                 __________________

          Syntax:  REWind

          Description:   The rewind  instruction rewinds  the tape  previously
               attached.

               Example:

                  * rewind

                  TAPE REWOUND

                  *




          2.1.20 Store Instruction                 _________________

          Syntax:  Store

          Description:   The store  instruction  rewinds  the tape  previously
               attached, and writes  the entire contents of the  CUD from disk
               on to the tape.

               Note:   This is  a very  time  consuming action  and cannot  be
               interrupted.

               Example:

                  * store

                  CUD STORED

                  *


                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 17


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



          2.1.21 Type All Instruction                 ____________________

          Syntax:  Type ALl

          Description:  The type all instruction lists the next GAN and UUN to
               be assigned and   all users in the CUD.   VAL outputs username,
               GAN and UUN for all valid users.

               Note:   This is  a very  time  consuming action  and cannot  be
               interrupted.

               Example:

                  * type all

                  NEXT GAN = 3
                  NEXT UUN = 5

                  BLOCK      USERNAME           GAN     UUN
                     3       FLAME                1       1
                   127       U273RCO              1       2
                   431       DOPLER               2       3
                  1012       MARCINJILL           2       4

                  *




          2.1.22 Type User Instruction                 _____________________

          Syntax:  Type User

          Description:  The  type user instruction  types out  all information
               about a user in the  CUD.   The  user only enters the username,
               and VAL  types GAN,  UUN, control  information, district,  IRC,
               password change date, and class or home information.

               Example:

                  * type user
                  USERNAME: marcinjill

                  GAN: 2
                  UUN: 4
                  LOGIN OVER SHUT
                  NO PASSWORD REQUIRED
                  DISTRICT: 4
                  IRC: 0
                  CLASS: 5
                  HOME GROUP: 2
                  *




