          SECTION 2.2 NETPRIV (Privileged) Instructions          _____________________________________________



          2.2.1 Get Instruction                _______________

          Syntax:  Get

          Description:  The get instruction types the  CUD block number that a
               username hashes  into.   The  user must enter the username, and
               the system returns a block number.

               Example:

                  * get
                  USERNAME: marcinj

                  BLOCK NUMBER: 400  (username marcinj is in block 400
                                     in CUD)
                  *



          2.2.2 Reset Command                _____________

          Syntax:  RESEt

          Description:  The reset instruction causes the checksums on each CUD
               block to be recalculated and CUD blocks rewritten to the disk.

               Note:  This is a  time consuming  action and  cannot be  inter-
                      rupted.

               Example:

                  * reset

                  CUD CHECKSUMS HAVE BEEN RESET

                  *


                                                       INSTRUCTIONS    Page 19


          VAL Users Guide                                   September 26, 1980



          2.2.3 Read CUD Instruction                ____________________

          Syntax:  REAd Cud

          Description:  The read  CUD instruction reads any block  of the CUD.
               The user must input the block number.

               Example:

                  * read

                  BLOCK NUMBER: 400

                  BLOCK READ
                  *




          2.2.4 Type CUD Instruction                ____________________

          Syntax:  Type Cud

          Description:  The type CUD instruction types  out the CUD block just
               read by  the read   CUD instruction.   The information  that is
               output includes username,  GAN, UUN, control  information, dis-
               trict, IRC,  password change date, and  home  or class informa-
               tion.  An index is also typed,  which is the user's location in
               the block.

               Example:

                 * type cud

                 USERNAME  GAN  UUN  CNTRL       DIST IRC PSW DATE INDEX

                 DOPLER      1    3   NOPW   TG    3    1  06/08/79   0
                 CLASS:  2 HOME HOST:     1
                 U273RCO     3    5   L>S IC       1    2  06/07/79   44
                 CLASS:  3 HOME GROUP:    6
                 *

               NOPW = no password required
               L>S = login over shut
               IC = ignore colon option











