          2.2.8 Type MUD Instruction                ____________________

          Syntax:  TYPE MUD

          Description:  The type MUD instruction types  out the MUD block just
               read by  the read MUD instruction.   The output is the  same as
               for type CUD.




          2.2.9 Write Instruction                _________________

          Syntax:  WRITE

          Description:  The write instruction is  used ***VERY carefully*** to
               overwrite MUD blocks with CUD information.  THIS IS A DANGEROUS
               COMMAND.

               Example:

               *WRITE

               ENTER SUP NUMBER:  124

               BLOCK WRITTEN

               *





