          2.2.10 MUD Consistency Command                 _______________________


          Syntax:  CONsistency

          Description:  This command used to cause  the MUD on a Supervisor to
               become identical with the CUD.

               Note:  This  command  requires considerable  time  to  complete
                      (sometimes 15 minutes or more).  The only way to stop it
                      once it  has begun is  to forcibly disconnect  from VAL.
                      It should be noted that the MUD will have been partially
                      updated at  that point.  As  the computer  processes the
                      blocks of information, a dot is  displayed on the termi-
                      nal after every  32 blocks of  the total 2040  are proc-
                      essed.

               Example:

               * CONSISTENCY

               ENTER SUP NO: 123

               .......................................................

               MUD CONSISTENCY COMPLETE

               *

               Note:  An optional terminal  message which may be  given to the
                      user in addition to MUD CONSISTENCY COMPLETE is

                      THERE WERE NO DIFFERENCES ENCOUNTERED.























