          SECTION 3.0 USER PASSWORD CHANGING          __________________________________

          VAL may be  configured to permit any  user with the colon  option to
          change his own password.  To log into VAL for this purpose, the user
          should enter his username  followed by a colon and  the change pass-
          word host number (a  configuration parameter), and a  semicolon fol-
          lowed by password.

               Example:
                                 marcinjill:83;password

          VAL will then inquire if the user  wishes to change his password and
          if so will request the password twice.  When the change is complete,
          the user will be logged off.

               Example:

               DO YOU WISH TO CHANGE YOUR PASSWORD? y

               PASSWORD:
               ENTER IT AGAIN:

               CHANGE COMPLETE
               PLEASE LOG IN:
































