          SECTION 4.0 FRONT PANEL DISPLAY          _______________________________

          While VAL is running, the Engine Front  Panel display may be used to
          display the  CUD block  number currently  in use.   This display  is
          selected by unlocking the Engine Front Panel, entering the slot num-
          ber in which  VAL is running and  then depressing the RUN  key.  The
          rightmost four digits are the current  CUD block number in hexadeci-
          mal.  This display is useful to monitor the progress of the consist-
          ency operation.  (CUD block numbers are between 0 and 7F8.)















































