          The following error messages are produced by VAL in response to var-
          ious erroneous  entries made  by a user.   Other error  messages may
          appear when running  VAL if there are system problems.   Most of the
          error messages are self-explanatory.  Those that are not self-expla-
          natory will have a brief explanation under the message.  The message
          is shown in uppercase  letters and the messages  are arranged alpha-
          betically.

          ALREADY ATTACHED

               A tape unit is already attached to this user's slot.

          BAD CHECKSUM - BLOCK 213

               A CUD block from the tape has an incorrect checksum.  The block
               is skipped in the restore operation.

          BAD PF AREA

               The PJ area on the disk is not properly set up.

          BYTE COUNT FROM ISIS DOES NOT MATCH RECORD BYTE COUNT

               A tape  record block count does  not match the  internal record
               count.

          CIRCUIT LOST

               The circuit to the other supervisor was lost.

          CIRCUIT NOT BUILT

               Unable to build a circuit to user UN2 on the supervisor.

          CANNOT DELETE LAST CLASS FOR A USER

               This only appears if the Class Information option has been cho-
               sen.

          CLASS NOT FOUND

               This only appears if the Class Information option has been cho-
               sen.

          CUD BUFFER EMPTY

               The CUD block read  has no data in it or no  CUD block has been
               read.








